Gluster 3.2: Configuring Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance for VMware[
Configuring Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance for VMware>>]

*To install the virtual storage appliance, perform the following steps.*

1.  Download the VMware Gluster Virtual Storage Appliance from
https://store.gluster.com/788/catalog/category.5837/language.en/currency.USD/?id=v3XNw3616z[here]. +
 +
 The *Gluster-Virtual-Storage-Appliance--3-2-0.ova* file will be
downloaded. +
 +
2.  Launch the VMware vSphere Client. The logon dialog appears. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-vsphere-client-logon.png.jpg[Client Logon] +
 +
3.  Logon to the client. The VMware vSphere Client main screen appears.
4.  Connect vSphere Client to an ESX, ESXi, or Virtual Center host, as
appropriate.
5.  Choose *File > Deploy OVF Template*. The Deploy OVF Template wizard
launches. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-vsphere-deploy.jpg.jpg[600px|File Deploy] +
 +
6.  Browse and select the downloaded file and click *Next*. +
 +
Image:Gluster-31-vsa-vsphere-source.jpg.jpg[ Source] +
 +
7.  Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the wizard. +
 +
Image:Gluster-32-vsa-vsphere-deploying.jpg.jpg[Deploying] +
 +
After you complete the wizard, the appliance is downloaded and added to
the ESX host virtual machine inventory.

